Arch Sofware Center
===================
A Simple Sofware center for Arch Linux Distribution

Main Features:
--------------
	- Uses pacman and AUR repositories (via yaourt?configurable pacman helper?)
	- Based on Python3 and PyQt(4/5?)
	- Very few Dependencies (just pacman, pyqt?)
	- Search for:
		- Exact Package Name First
		- Description (from https://www.archlinux.org/packages/ and AUR)
		- Categories
		- Installed or Not
		- Updates
		- Local .desktop files installed user apps
	- Offline Search
	- Uses QWebView for display in HTML:
		- Icons
		- Package Name
		- Description
		- Screenshots
		- Categories
		- Installed
			- Button to Update
			- Button to uninstall
			- Button to run
		- Not Installed
			- Button to install
		- Access to Wiki Related Articles

- References/Related:
---------------------
	- Pacman (https://wiki.archlinux.org/index.php/Pacman_Rosetta)
	- AUR (https://www.digitalocean.com/community/tutorials/how-to-use-yaourt-to-easily-download-arch-linux-community-packages)
	- Yaourt (https://github.com/archlinuxfr/yaourt)
	- Python
	- PyQt
	- QWebkit
	- Getting events from QWebView to python
	- Arch packages info to JSON: https://wiki.archlinux.org/index.php/Official_repositories_web_interface
	- AurJson (https://wiki.archlinux.org/index.php/AurJson)
	- Similar(¿Contribute?) to yoimnotpro (https://aur.archlinux.org/packages/yoimnotpro/)
	- Desktop Entries (Gendesk) (https://wiki.archlinux.org/index.php/Desktop_entries)
	- Open Icon Library (http://sourceforge.net/p/openiconlibrary)
	- AppStream: tool for creating Sofware Centers (https://www.archlinux.org/packages/?q=appstream)
	- Pkgfile: for search info of non-instaled pkgs (https://wiki.archlinux.org/index.php/Pkgfile)
	- Packagekit: for install packages (https://www.archlinux.org/packages/community/x86_64/packagekit/)
	- Package-Query https://github.com/archlinuxfr/package-query/
	- For packaging: https://wiki.archlinux.org/index.php/Creating_packages
	- Pbget: get backage builds from ABS and AUR

